    {
      "id": "1ac4750c-f3ba-803a-96fb-f3e0ef38c07e",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors use different NLP on course names as part of the features in a course sequence recommender system. Results show that naming convention actually is useful for the models and the authors expand in the different ways that similarity can be computed to measure distance between courses.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
